    <stitle>RADIATOR, REMOVE AND REPLACE - MXT - RADIATOR and Component INSTALLation</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>RADIATOR and Component INSTALLation</title>
        <svcproc svcproctype="install" graphiccount="1">
            <title>RADIATOR CORE</title>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>Please refer to the Torque Tables in this manual for specific torque requirements.</para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>The entire Radiator Assembly/Cooling Module consists of: Radiator Core, Radiator Frame, Charge
                        Air Cooler (CAC), AC Condenser and Fan Shroud.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Place radiator lower frame assembly in position to install radiator core.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Place one side of radiator frame assembly on lower frame and install lower bolts.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install core assembly, position and align bolt holes for side frame and radiator core.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install bolts and hand tighten.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Locate and install charge air cooler in frame assembly (Figure 27).</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install mounting bolts in charge air cooler.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install opposite side frame, align and install fan shroud to side frames, and install
                    and tighten bolts in side frame and radiator.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install radiator top frame and fasten top frame to side frame sections.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">With radiator supported, attach lifting sling to top or radiator lifting points.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Locate radiator on chassis frame radiator mounting blocks.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Insert bolts in radiator mounting blocks and bracket, and tighten bolts.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Check the alignment of the radiator on frame rails.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Loosen and remove lifting sling and hoist.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Locate and attach stabilizer rods to support radiator on bumper structure assembly.
                </para>
            </step1>
